{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. This version of the library introduced 1 new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"API, as well as beta support for Swift Testing.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this migration guide be sure you have fully migrated to the newest","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tools of version 1.11. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for more information."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Custom file storage coding","anchor":"Custom-file-storage-coding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.10 of the Composable Architecture introduced a powerful tool for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"sharing state","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"sharing state"},{"type":"text","text":" amongst your features, and included several built-in persistence"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strategies, including file storage. This strategy, however, was not very flexible, and only"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"supported the default JSON encoding and decoding offered by Swift.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this version, you can now define custom encoding and decoding logic using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage(_:decode:encode:)"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Swift-Testing","text":"Swift Testing","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode 16 and Swift 6 come with a powerful new native testing framework. Existing test targets using","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"XCTest can even incrementally adopt the framework and define new tests with Testing. Existing XCTest","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"helpers","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", however, are not compatible with the new framework, and so test tools like the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Composable Architecture’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore"},{"text":" did not work with it out of the box.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That changes with this version, which seamlessly supports XCTest "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Swift’s Testing framework."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"You can now create a test store in a "},{"code":"@Test","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and failures will be reported accordingly."}]}]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.12"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Take advantage of custom decoding and encoding logic for the shared file storage persistence","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strategy, as well as beta support for Swift’s native Testing framework."}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits"